The '''Pittsburgh Science of Learning Center''' (''aka'' LearnLab) is a Science of Learning Center funded by the [[National Science Foundation]] and managed by [[Carnegie Mellon University]] and the [[University of Pittsburgh]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nsf.gov/awardsearch/showAward.do?AwardNumber=0354420 |title=Award#0354420 - SLC Center: Pittsburgh Science of Learning Center: Studying Robust Learning with Learning Experiments in Real Classrooms |publisher=Nsf.gov |date= |accessdate=2011-10-24}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://psychcentral.com/news/archives/2004-10/cmu-cmu100404.html |title=Carnegie Mellon, University of Pittsburgh receive NSF grant to create Science of Learning Center |publisher=Psych Central |date=2009-02-21 |accessdate=2011-10-24 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140513011233/http://psychcentral.com/news/archives/2004-10/cmu-cmu100404.html |archivedate=2014-05-13 |df= }}</ref> The PSLC is led by [[Kenneth Koedinger]] and [[Charles Perfetti]], and includes many other notable scientists, including [[Vincent Aleven]] and [[David Klahr]].
The PSLC theory wiki collects and organizes research results, including a list of instructional principles that are supported by learning science research. The wiki is open and freely editable.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.learnlab.org/research/wiki/index.php/Instructional_Principles_and_Hypotheses |title=Instructional Principles and Hypotheses - Pslc |publisher=Learnlab.org |date=2011-09-08 |accessdate=2011-10-24}}</ref>
Several notable tools, methods, and theories were developed at the PSLC, including the [[PSLC DataShop]]/[[LearnSphere]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.learnlab.org/datashop |title=PSLC DataShop |publisher=Learnlab.org |date=2011-09-08 |accessdate=2016-10-21}}</ref> the Knowledge-Learning-Instruction Framework,<ref>{{cite journal | url = http://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/10.1111/j.1551-6709.2012.01245.x/abstract | title = The Knowledge‐Learning‐Instruction framework: Bridging the science‐practice chasm to enhance robust student learning | last1 = Koedinger| first1 = Kenneth| last2 = Corbett| first2 = Albert| last3 = Perfetti| first3 = Charles | date = 2012 | journal = Cognitive Science| publisher = Wiley | volume= 36 |issue= 5 | doi=10.1111/j.1551-6709.2012.01245.x}}</ref> and the [[Baker Rodrigo Ocumpaugh Monitoring Protocol]].
